<li class="commentbody" id="comment-122948">
			<cite>Lauren</cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-122948" title="">July 24, 2008</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">53</div>

				<p>I have long worshiped at the alter of biscotti sans butter(makes the best &#8220;crunch&#8221;) and have developed a trick for working with the sticky dough that results: lay out a piece of parchment on your work surface that is wider than your baking sheet and flour liberally. Mold biscotti dough into desired rectangular shape. Put baking sheet upside down on parchment. Pull excess parchment tight over the baking sheet and flip! Pull parchment off of dough (there should only be minimal stickage). This trick allows you to work the dough into the proper shape without it sticking to your work surface and making a transfer to the baking sheet impossible. Hope this helps. Thanks for the beautiful pics Deb.</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
<li class="commentbody highlighted" id="comment-122949">
			<cite><a href='http://smittenkitchen.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>deb</a></cite>
